Usage: set_via_pillars [-help] <stackViaRule>* [-required {0 | 1 | 2 | 3 |4}] {-term <term|term> | -instterm <instTerm|pgInstTerm>}

-help                               # Prints out the command usage
<stackViaRule>*                     # A list of via pillars (for term) or a
                                    # single via pillar (for instTerm).
                                    # ((stackViaRule)*, required)
-instterm <instTerm|pgInstTerm>     # InstTerm name or pointer.
                                    # ((instTerm|pgInstTerm), required)
-required {0 | 1 | 2 | 3 |4}        # Specify whether stack vias are required
                                    # for this term or instTerm. For term, the
                                    # value can be 0/1/2/3/4, for instTerm, the
                                    # value can be 0/1.
                                    # (int, optional, min=0, max=4)
-term <term|term>                   # Term name or pointer.
                                    # ((term|term), required)